.TH MSH 1 "2 November 2021" "manual page for Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple Shell for ALX
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./msh
[command] [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is one of the projects for ALX  where we explore and build a functional simple shell program.

The shell is a command that reads lines from either a file or the terminal, interprets them, and generally executes other commands. It is the program that is running when a super logs into the system.

.B Overview

The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter similar to
.B bash or
.B dash.
.I FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.B Simple Shell
operates in both
.I interactive
and 
.I non-interactive
mode. The user may initiate
.B simple shell
and begin working or initate
.B simple shell
using commands meant to be run by the program.
.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument, argument 0 is understood to be the program/command to be run by
.B simple shell
and arguments following as modifier or options.
.SH Return value
The return value of a simple command is its exit status
.SH Example
.PP

$./msh

$

$ls - This lists all the files and folders in the current working directory.

